  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nOn older cpus some have issues supporting blst.\r\n\r\n**Adding the following flags during build allows compatibility:**\r\n```\r\nCGO_CFLAGS: \"-O -D__BLST_PORTABLE__\"\r\nCGO_CFLAGS_ALLOW: \"-O -D__BLST_PORTABLE__\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n**REFERENCE:**\r\nhttps://github.com/bnb-chain/bsc/issues/1562\r\nhttps://github.com/bnb-chain/bsc/pull/1575/commits/54ea7feb2c3eee397b3534f1e636387b37d812d7\n\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\n\n_No response_\n\n### ðŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction\n\n_No response_\n\n### Error\n\n```text\nCaught SIGILL in blst_cgo_init, consult <blst>/bindinds/go/README.md.\n```\n\n\n### Platform(s)\n\nLinux (x86)\n\n### What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)\n\n4.0.8\n\n### Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?\n\n_No response_",
